item.title: Blackboards: Warwick Barbell Management
item.description: Blackboards is a website written for Warwick Barbell during my time as the powerlifting captain. It handles registration for club sessions, displaying member personal bests and running the annual position elections.

item.title: Fisherman: Continuous Deployment
item.description: Fisherman is a continuous deployment tool mainly targeted at Rust projects that listens for GitHub webhooks to rebuild and deploy changes.

item.title: ptc: Experimental Python to C Compiler
item.description: ptc is an experimental compiler that converts Python source code into the C language and was written as my dissertation project.

item.title: Sybl: Accessible Machine Learning through Ensemble Learning
item.description: Sybl is an accessible platform that allows users with low technical experience to gain the benefits of machine learning by providing data. Clients provide models for training and are reimbursed based on their performance on the problem.
